Description:
We have a stimulating environment where our people are empowered to do meaningful work with like-
minded colleagues that want to win. We have embraced a digital first, remote work model that includes work
from anywhere (YES! We mean it!). We have invested in systems, in tools, in process because we care about
doing things right, better and faster. We welcome anyone that has this same drive and that wants to help us
win.
It’s nice to meet you – we can’t wait for you to join and make a difference!
ACCOUNTING /OPERATIONS ANALYST
The accounting analyst assists his/her team in the preparation of financial results, budgets and other financial
analyzes required.
Responsibilities
• Active participant of month end review meeting, providing critical analysis
Prepare and / or revise end-of-month reconciliations;
Preparing government remittances and bank reconciliations;
Ensure the validity, accuracy and integrity of the financial information presented;
Maintain financial reporting structures in the accounting information system;
Plan and participate in the end-of-year audit process;
Carry out any financial analyzes required.
Qualifications
Accounting or relevant work experience related to the position;
Bachelor’s degree in accounting or related field;
Advance computer skills in Excel;
Focused on detail and results;
Capable of carrying out several projects within a limited timeframe;
Excellent organizational skills;
Be able to work independently with minimal supervision;
Capable of responding to changing priorities;
Excellent communication and leadership skills;
Bilingual (French / English);
2 to 3 years experience in a similar position.
Eager to make a difference? Send us your resume to
hr@bouclair.com
Only selected candidates will be contacted.
Bouclair is committed to the employment equity principle.
The masculine is used without discrimination and solely to lighten the text.
Who we are.
Based in Montreal, Bouclair is a lifestyle brand with a unique offering of in-house designed home fashion
décor and furniture. Our 900+ employees are all committed to deliver on our promise to inspire our
customers thanks to beautiful product, exceptional shopping experiences and aspirational environments in
our 54 stores across Canada and online.
